{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Labs Snow Buildup"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 22], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [135, 200], "text": [" Adds geometry to an input mesh that mimics snow buildup "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [200, 289], "text": ["This is a sample node for a common Houdini use case, modify at will to fit your needs. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [289, 421], "text": ["One of the classic Houdini problems is to generate Snow Caps over objects. But there was no built in solution for this until now. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [421, 584], "text": ["This works by scattering points on up facing polygons of the incoming mesh, copying some spheres onto those points and then voxelizing and smoothing the result. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [584, 690], "text": ["This was original designed and used on our GDC 2019 Unity demo and subsequently released to the public. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [690, 724], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/snow_buildup.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/snow_buildup.png"}]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [783, 908], "text": ["How far the snow will wrap around the object. 180 means full hemisphere, 0 means only surfaces perfectly facing up. "]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Spread Angle"], "role": "item", "extent": [765, 783], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [935, 991], "text": ["How many snow drops to generate on the surface "]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Number of Snow Points"], "role": "item", "extent": [908, 935], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1017, 1083], "text": ["Size range on each snow drop, which turns into a sphere. "]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Point Size (Min/Max)"], "role": "item", "extent": [991, 1017], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Scattering Options"], "extent": [736, 765], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1132, 1162], "text": ["Blur the snow volume "]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Smooth Iterations"], "role": "item", "extent": [1109, 1132], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1180, 1219], "text": ["Grow or Shrink the snow volume"]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Dilate/Erode"], "role": "item", "extent": [1162, 1180], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1244, 1288], "text": ["Blur the final generated snow mesh "]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Blurring Iterations"], "role": "item", "extent": [1219, 1244], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1299, 1340], "text": ["Vertex Colors on the output mesh"]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Color"], "role": "item", "extent": [1288, 1299], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Meshing Options"], "extent": [1083, 1109], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1382, 1428], "text": ["Limit the snow mesh to this polycount"]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Reduce to # Polys"], "role": "item", "extent": [1359, 1382], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1458, 1546], "text": ["Remove faces that are inside the interior mesh by boolean the 2 meshes together"]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Boolean Against Original"], "role": "item", "extent": [1428, 1458], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 